    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-27T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-27T22:00:00-05:00" n="661"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760F.62/1147a Supp.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-27T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 27, 1938—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. Please report immediately whether the President’s first appeal was carried
                    in part or in whole by the press or radio in Berlin. Also report subsequently
                    whether the message transmitted to Chancellor Hitler tonight<note n="89"
                        xml:id="d661fn89">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> by the President is carried by the
                    German press or radio.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
